              <td align="left" valign="top"><h1>Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
                  <p><strong>Eligible  Vehicles</strong> - Motor  driven Vehicles owned by You and Registered with Us with a weight rating  of up to 1 &frac12; tons designed, licensed and used for on road transportation.&nbsp;  Registration must be completed with Us at least 24 hours prior to the time of Disablement to be  eligible to receive Benefits.</p>
                  <p> <strong>Maximum Usage</strong> - Service is  limited to one (1) use in any 72 hour period and limited to three (3) uses within the twelve (12) month  period following the date of Your qualified N2 PLUS ROADSIDE CARE Tire  Protection Plan purchase.&nbsp; </p>
                  <p><strong>No Additional Fees</strong> - All  Plan Benefits are available to Your up to the Benefit Limit without any additional  payment or fees. You are responsible for any non-covered expenses or any  expenses over Your Plan or Benefit Limit.&nbsp; Your N2 PLUS  ROADSIDE CARE Tire Protection Plan Plan must be current to be eligible for any  Benefits.</p>
                  <p><strong>Eligible Members and Use of Plan</strong> &ndash; Coverage  and Plan Benefits is provided to You and Your Vehicle. This Plan  is non-transferable. You agree that only You in Your  Vehicle may use Your Plan. You will promptly notify Us if You  become aware of any unauthorized use of Your Plan or Identification  number, or if Your Identification number is lost or stolen. </p>
                  <p><strong>Plan Term</strong> - The  Plan term begins on the date shown on Your receipt of Your N2  PLUS ROADSIDE CARE Tire Protection Plan purchase and will continue until  midnight on the 365th day from the date of purchase, unless  cancelled by You, Us or the N2 PLUS ROADSIDE CARE Tire Protection Plan  company.</p>
                  <p><strong>Plan Renewal </strong>&ndash; For Your  convenience and to avoid any lapse in Coverage, Your Plan  can be renewed at the end of Your Plan Term by returning to Your  N2 PLUS ROADSIDE CARE Tire Protection Plan dealer and purchasing another  qualified N2 PLUS ROADSIDE CARE Tire Protection Plan product. </p>
                  <p><strong>Plan Cancellation / Transfer</strong> - Your Plan  will automatically terminate at midnight on the 365th day following  the date of purchase of Your qualified N2 PLUS ROADSIDE CARE Tire  Protection Plan product.&nbsp; We may cancel Your Plan upon written  notice for the following reasons; a) unauthorized use, fraud, abuse, or b)  notification from the N2 PLUS ROADSIDE CARE Tire Protection Plan Company that Your  qualified N2 PLUS ROADSIDE CARE Tire Protection Plan product has been cancelled  or returned. This membership is provided at no additional cost to you and therefore it is non-cancelable  and non-transferable  by the plan holder.</p>
                  <p><strong>The following items are not  included as part of the emergency roadside assistance benefit:</strong> Any  Benefit not listed herein, Cost of parts, replacement keys, fluids,  lubricants, or fuel, cost of installation of products, or materials.  Non-emergency towing or other non-emergency service. Any service available  through a valid manufacturer's warranty or service.&nbsp; Mounting or removing  of snow tires or chains.&nbsp; Shoveling snow from around a vehicle. Tire  Repair. Trucks over one and a half ton capacity, antique vehicles (meaning  vehicles over 20 years old or out of manufacture for 10 years or more),  taxicabs, limousines, or other commercial vehicles.&nbsp; Camping trailers,  travel trailers, or any vehicles in tow.&nbsp; Any and all taxes, fines.&nbsp;  Towing from or repair work performed at a service station, garage or repair  shop.&nbsp; Towing by other than a licensed service station or garage; vehicle  storage charges; a second tow.&nbsp; Service on a vehicle that is not in a safe  condition to be towed. Towing or service on roads not regularly maintained,  such as sand beaches, open fields, forests, and areas designated as not  passable due to construction, etc.&nbsp; Vehicles designed specifically for or  used off-road.&nbsp; Towing at the direction of a law enforcement officer  relating to traffic obstruction, impoundment, abandonment, illegal parking, or  other violations of law.&nbsp; Services secured independently of Us.&nbsp; This  is not a reimbursement Plan.&nbsp; Benefits are not applicable if disablement  is due to an act of God, war, insurrection, riot, etc. </p>
                  <p><strong>Service Provider Network</strong> - We  operate through a network of contracted service providers who have agreements  with Us to perform road and towing service for Our Members.&nbsp; As  independent contractors, they have exclusive control over their own equipment and  personnel.&nbsp; We are not responsible for their acts or omissions.&nbsp; WE  MAKE NO WARRANTIES, EXPRESSED OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING THE WARRANTY OF  MERCHANTABILITY OR FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, WITH RESPECT TO ANY OF THE  PLAN BENEFITS OR RELATED INFORMATION PROVIDED TO YOU. OUR LIABILITY  SHALL NOT EXCEED YOUR CURRENT PLAN FEE AND, UNDER NO CIRCUMSTANCES,  SHALL WE BE LIABLE FOR YOUR INCIDENTAL OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES. (b) We  reserve the right to eliminate, add, and change participating providers without  notice.&nbsp; During extreme weather conditions, there may be some delay before  help can reach You. Vehicle must be accessible from a normally traveled  roadway.                  </p>
                  <h2>*For complete details of Terms and Conditions please refer to plan Terms and Conditions received at time of registration.</h2>
